7
[div class=p 
	"This year was quite productive regarding the games based on the classic horror heroes: Dracula and Frankenstein, based on 1990th movie adaptations. 4 games have been covered: Frankenstein for 
	$LF
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Genesis|href=/5833M)
	" and 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Sega CD|href=/5831M)
	", and Dracula for 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=NES|href=/6149M)
	" and 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Gameboy|href=/6135M)
	". I decided to join the coincidental marathon, beat Dracula for Sega CD and obsolete my old slow-motion TAS I made in 2013 (
	[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8__altBSe-k rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"part 1
	]a
	" and 
	[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UJBfSBxCujE rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"part 2
	]a
	").
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Not much to say about the game. It's side-scrolling beat 'em up, where you go from left to right while beating and dodging animals and monsters, with a boss at the end. I'd say, it's one of the worst games among those which have a similar gameplay.
	$LF
]div
